dle of blood beneath his head, not a puddle of wine. The second turnkey had managed to push back from the bench and draw his dagger before someone shoved a longsword through his ribs. His had been the longer, messier end. }{\cs28\i 
I told Varys no one was to be harmed in this escape,}{ Jaime thought, }{\cs28\i but I should have told my brother and my sister.}{ \'93This was ill done, ser.\'94 
