\par \'93How would I know? There could be a hundred reasons.\'94 
\par \'93Or one. Are you aware that the Golden Company has broken its contract with Myr?\'94 
\par \'93Sellswords break their contracts all the time.\'94 
\par \'93Not the Golden Company. }{\cs28\i Our word is good as gold}{ has been their boast since the days of Bittersteel. Myr is on the point of war with Lys and Tyrosh. Why break a contract that offered them the prospect of good wages and good plunder?\'94 

\par \'93Perhaps Lys offered them better wages. Or Tyrosh.\'94 
\par \'93No,\'94 she said. \'93I would believe it of any of the other free companies, yes. Most of them would change sides for half a groat. The Golden Company is different. A brotherhood of exiles and the sons of exiles, united by the dream of Bittersteel. It
\rquote s home they want, as much as gold. Lord Yronwood knows that as well as I do. His forebears rode with Bittersteel during three of the Blackfyre Rebellions.\'94 She took Ser Arys by the hand, and wove her fingers through his own. \'93
Have you ever seen the arms of House Toland of Ghost Hill?\'94 
\par He had to think a moment. \'93A dragon eating its own tail?\'94 
\par \'93The dragon is time. It has no beginning and no ending, so all things come round again. Anders Yronwood is Criston Cole reborn. He whispers in my brother\rquote s ear that }{\cs28\i he}{
 should rule after my father, that it is not right for men to kneel to women . . . that Arianne especially is unfit to rule, being the willful wanton that she is.\'94 She tossed her hair defiantly. \'93
So your two princesses share a common cause, ser . . . and they share as well a knight who claims to love them both, but will not fight for them.\'94 
\par \'93I will.\'94 Ser Arys sank to one knee. \'93Myrcella }{\cs28\i is}{ the elder, and better suited to the crown. Who will defend her rights if not her Kingsguard? My sword, my life, my honor, all belong to her . . . and to you, my heart\rquote 
s delight. I swear, no man will steal your birthright whilst I still have the strength to lift a sword. I am yours. What would you have of me?\'94 
\par \'93All.\'94 She knelt to kiss his lips. \'93}{\cs28\i All,}{ my love, my true love, my sweet love, and forever. But first . . .\'94 
\par \'93Ask, and it is yours.\'94 
\par \'93. . . Myrcella.\'94
