\par And when they reached the Arbor, things had gone from bad to worse. Lord Redwyne\rquote s twin sons had desp
ised Sam on first sight. Every morn they found some fresh way to shame him in the practice yard. On the third day Horas Redwyne made him squeal like a pig when he begged for quarter. On the fifth his brother Hobber clad a kitchen girl in his own armor and
