\par Laughter sounded from behind them. She ripped Oathkeeper from her sheath and whirled, expecting more Bloody Mummers . . . but it was only Hyle Hunt atop the crumbling wall, his legs crossed. \'93If there are brothels down i
n hell, the wretch will thank you,\'94 the knight called down. \'93Elsewise, that\rquote s a waste of good gold.\'94 
\par \'93I keep my promises. What are }{\cs28\i you}{ doing here?\'94 
\par \'93Lord Randyll bid me follow you. If by some freak\rquote s chance you stumbled onto Sansa Stark, he told me to bring her back to Maidenpool. Have no fear, I was commanded not to harm you.\'94 
\par Brienne snorted. \'93As if you could.\'94 
\par \'93What will you do now, my lady?\'94 
\par \'93Cover him.\'94 
\par \'93About the girl, I meant. The Lady Sansa.\'94 
\par Brienne thought a moment. \'93She was making for Riverrun, if Timeon told it true. Somewhere along the way she was taken by the Hound. If I find him . . .\'94 
\par \'93. . . he\rquote ll kill you.\'94 
\par \'93Or I\rquote ll kill him,\'94 she said stubbornly. \'93Will you help me cover up poor Crabb, ser?\'94 
