\par Outside, the sun was setting. Dorcas had prepared a bath for her. The queen was so
aking pleasantly in the warm water and contemplating what she would say to her supper guests when Jaime came bursting through the door and ordered Jocelyn and Dorcas from the room. Her brother looked rather less than immaculate and had a smell of horse ab
