\par Jaime was still laughing. The queen ignored him. \'93Tommen, come here.\'94 When he hung back, she sighed. \'93Are you afraid? A king should not show fear.\'94 The boy approached the tub, his eyes downcast. She reached out and stroked his golden curls. 
\'93King or no, you are a little boy. Until you come of age, the rule is mine. You }{\cs28\i will}{ learn to joust, I promise you. But not from Loras. The knights of the Kingsguard have more important duties than playing wit
