 the queen reflected. It had been a long day, and Taena\rquote s wit always cheered her. Cersei had not had a friend she so enjoyed since Melara Hetherspoon, and Melara had turned out to be a greedy little schemer with ideas above her station. }{\cs28\i 
I should not think ill of her. She\rquote s dead and drowned, and she taught me never to trust anyone but Jaime.}{ 
\par By the time she joined them in the solar, her guests had made a good start on the hippocras. }{\cs28\i Lady Falyse not only looks like a fish, she drinks like one,}{ she reflected, when she made note of the half-empty flagon. \'93Sweet Falyse,\'94
