\par Sh
e was ten when she finally saw her prince in the flesh, at the tourney her lord father had thrown to welcome King Aerys to the west. Viewing stands had been raised beneath the walls of Lannisport, and the cheers of the smallfolk had echoed off Casterly Ro
ck like rolling thunder. }{\cs28\i They cheered Father twice as loudly as they cheered the king,}{ the queen recalled, }{\cs28\i but only half as loudly as they cheered Prince Rhaegar. }{
