s Rebellion and Prince Rhaegar could not be found, Aerys had turned to the next best thing, and raise
d Connington to the Handship. But the Mad King was always chopping off his Hands. He had chopped Lord Jon after the Battle of the Bells, stripping him of honors, lands, and wealth, and packing him off across the sea to die in exile, where he soon drank hi
mself to death. The cousin, though\emdash Red Ronnet\rquote s father\emdash had joined the rebellion and been rewarded with Griffin\rquote 
