\par \'93Best keep it to yourself. The hill is thick with sparrows, and we all know how sparrows abhor wickedness.\'94 
\par \'93I have heard they abhor soap and water too, Your Grace.\'94 
\par \'93Perhaps too much prayer robs a man of his sense of smell. I shall be sure to ask His High Holiness.\'94 
\par The draperies swayed back and forth in a wash of crimson silk. \'93Orton told me that the High Septon has no name,\'94 Lady Taena said. \'93Can that be true? In Myr we all have names.\'94 
\par \'93Oh, he had a name }{\cs28\i once.}{ They all do.\'94 The queen waved a hand dismissively. \'93Even septons born of noble blood go only by their given names once they have taken their vows. When one of them is elevated to }{\cs28\i High}{
 Septon, he puts aside that name as well. The Faith will tell you he no longer has any need of a man\rquote s name, for he has become the avatar of the gods.\'94 
\par \'93How do you distinguish one High Septon from another?\'94 
