\par The litter began to slow, which could only mean that they were near the top of the hill. \'93You should bring this son of yours to court,\'94 Cersei told Lady Merryweather. \'93Six is not too young. Tommen needs other boys about him. Why not your son?\'94
 Joffrey had never had a close friend of his own age, that she recalled. }{\cs28\i The poor boy was always alone. I had Jaime when I was a child . . . and Melara, until she fell into the well.}{
