\par The queen pulled back a corner of the curtain and beckoned to Ser Meryn Trant. \'93What seems to be the trouble?\'94 
\par \'93The sparrows, Your Grace.\'94 Ser Meryn wore white scale armor beneath his cloak. His helm and shield were slung from his saddle. \'93Camping in the street. We\rquote ll make them move.\'94 
\par \'93Do that, but gently. I do not care to be caught up in another riot.\'94 Cersei let the curtain fall. \'93This is absurd.\'94 
\par \'93It is, Your Grace,\'94 Lady Merryweather agreed. \'93The High Septon should have come to you. And these wretched sparrows . . .\'94 
\par \'93He feeds them, coddles them, }{\cs28\i blesses}{ them. Yet will not bless the king.\'94 The blessing was an empty ritual
, she knew, but rituals and ceremonies had power in the eyes of the ignorant. Aegon the Conqueror himself had dated the start of his realm from the day the High Septon anointed him in Oldtown. \'93
This wretched priest will obey, or learn how weak and human he still is.\'94 
