d asked for. He had lost six ships, and captured eight-and-thirty. \'93It will serve,\'94 he told Nute. \'93To the oars. We return to Lord Hewett\rquote s Town.\'94 
\par His oarsmen bent their backs toward Oakenshield, and the iron captain went belowdecks once again. \'93I could kill him,\'94 he told the dusky woman. \'93Though it is a great sin to kill your king, and a worse one to kill your brother.\'94 He frowned. \'93
Asha should have given me her voice.\'94 How could she have ever hoped to win the captains and the kings, her with her pinecones and her turnips? }{\cs28\i Balon\rquote s blood is in her, but she is still a woman.}{ She had run after the kingsmoot. The
