aldic finery. His arms and legs had been tied to his chair, and a huge white radish shoved between his teeth so he could not speak . . . though he could see and hear. The Crow\rquote s Eye had claimed the place of honor at his lordship\rquote 
s right hand. A pretty, buxom girl of seventeen or eighteen years was in his lap, barefoot and disheveled, her arms around his neck. \'93Who is that?\'94 Victarion asked the men around him. 
\par \'93His lordship\rquote s bastard daughter,\'94 laughed Hotho. \'93Before Euron took the castle, she was made to wait at table on the rest and take her own meals with the servants.\'94 
\par Euron put his blue lips to her throat, and the girl giggled and whispered something in his ear. Smiling, he kissed her throat again. Her white skin was covered with red marks where his mo
uth had been; they made a rosy necklace about her neck and shoulders. Another whisper in his ear, and this time the Crow\rquote s Eye laughed aloud, then slammed his wine cup down for silence. \'93Good ladies,\'94
