Rise, Maron Volmark, Lord of Greenshield.\'94 A beardless boy of six-and-ten years, Volmark stood hesitantly, looking like the lord of rabbits. \'93And rise, Nute the Barber, Lord of Oakenshield.\'94 
\par Nute\rquote s eyes grew wary, as if he feared he was the butt of some cruel jape. \'93A lord?\'94 he croaked. 
\par Victarion had expected the Crow\rquote s Eye to give the lordships to his own creatures, Stonehand and the Red Oarsman and Left-Hand Lucas Codd. }{\cs28\i A king must needs be open-handed,}{ he tried to tell himself, but another voice whispered, }{
\cs28\i Euron\rquote s gifts are poisoned.}{ When he turned it over in his head, he saw it plain. }{\cs28\i The Knight was the Reader\rquote 
s chosen heir, and Andrik the Unsmiling the strong right arm of Dunstan Drumm. Volmark is a callow boy, but he has Black Harren\rquote s blood in him through his mother. And the Barber . . . }{
\par Victarion grabbed him by the forearm. \'93Refuse him!\'94 
\par Nute looked at him as if he had gone mad. \'93Refuse him? Lands and lordship? Will }{\cs28\i you}{ make me a lord?\'94 He wrenched his arm away and stood, basking in the cheers. 
