rd. Emm has it in his pointed head that he will rule the riverlands. And Lancel . . . I suppose we should have seen this coming from afar. A life protecting the High Septon is not so different from a life protecting the king, after all. Kevan will be wrot
h, I fear. As wroth as Tywin was when you got it in your head to take the white. At least Kevan still has Martyn for an heir. He can marry him to Gatehouse Ami in Lancel\rquote s place. Seven save us all.\'94 His aunt gave a sigh. \'93
And speaking of the Seven, why would Cersei permit the Faith to arm again?\'94 
