\par \'93Do you still grieve for this friend of your childhood?\'94 Qyburn asked. \'93Is that what troubles you, Your Grace?\'94 
\par \'93Melara? No. I can hardly recall what she looked like. It is just . . . the }{\cs28\i maegi}{ knew how many children I would have, and she knew of Robert\rquote s bastards. Years before he\rquote 
d sired even the first of them, she knew. She promised me I should be queen, but said another queen would come . . .\'94 }{\cs28\i Younger and more beautiful, she said. }{\'93. . . another queen, who would take from me all I loved.\'94 
\par \'93And you wish to forestall this prophecy?\'94 
\par }{\cs28\i More than anything,}{ she thought. \'93}{\cs28\i Can}{ it be forestalled?\'94 
\par \'93Oh, yes. Never doubt that.\'94 
\par \'93How?\'94 
\par \'93I think Your Grace knows how.\'94 
