\par \'93Twenty times the men require twenty times the food. How well are you provisioned, my lord?\'94 
\par \'93Well enough to sit here till the end of days if need be, whilst you starve inside your walls.\'94 He told the lie as boldly as he could and hoped his face did not betray him. 
\par The Blackfish was not deceived. \'93The end of your days, perhaps. Our own supplies are ample, though I fear we did not leave much in the fields for visitors.\'94 
\par \'93We can bring food down from the Twins,\'94 said Jaime, \'93or over the hills from the west, if it comes to that.\'94 
\par \'93If you say so. Far be it from me to question the word of such an honorable knight.\'94 
