\par \'93It\rquote s you I want.\'94 
\par That was the right answer. \'93First you must confess your treason. A man\rquote s sins can poison his soul if left to fester. I know it must be hard for you to live with what you\rquote ve done. It is past time that you rid yourself of your shame.\'94 

\par \'93Shame?\'94 Osney sounded baffled. \'93I told Osmund, Margaery just teases. She never lets me do any more than . . .\'94 
\par \'93It is chivalrous of you to protect her,\'94 Cersei broke in, \'93but you are too good a knight to go on living with your crime. No, you must take yourself to the Great Sept of Baelor this very night and speak with the High Septon. When a man\rquote 
s sins are so black, only His High Holiness himself can save him from hell\rquote s torments. Tell him how you bedded Margaery and her cousins.\'94 
\par Osney blinked. \'93What, the cousins too?\'94 
\par \'93Megga and Elinor,\'94 she decided, \'93never Alla.\'94 That little detail would make the whole story more plausible. \'93Alla would sit weeping, and plead with the others to stop their sinning.\'94 
\par \'93Just Megga and Elinor? Or Margaery too?\'94 
\par \'93Margaery, most certainly. She was the one behind it all.\'94 
\par She told him all she had in mind. As Osney listened, apprehension slowly spread across his face. When she finished he said, \'93After you cut her head off, I want to take that kiss she never gave me.\'94 
\par \'93You may take all the kisses you like.\'94 
\par \'93And then the Wall?\'94 
\par \'93For just a little while. Tommen is a forgiving king.\'94 
\par Osney scratched at his scarred cheek. \'93Usually if I lie about some woman, it\rquote s me saying how I never fucked them and them saying how I did. This . . . I never lied to no }{\cs28\i High Septon}{ before. I think you go to some hell for that. One o
\rquote  the bad ones.\'94 
\par The queen was taken aback. The last thing she expected was piety from a Kettleblack. \'93Are you refusing to obey me?\'94 
\par \'93No.\'94 Osney touched her golden hair. \'93The thing is, the best lies have some truth in \rquote em . . . to give \rquote em flavor, as it were. And you want me to go tell how I fucked a queen . . .\'94 
\par She almost slapped his face. Almost. But she had gone too far, and too much was at stake. }{\cs28\i All I do, I do for Tommen.}{ She turned her head and caught Ser Osney\rquote s hand with her own, kissing his fingers. They were rough and
 hard, callused from the sword. }{\cs28\i Robert had hands like that,}{ she thought. 
\par Cersei wrapped her arms about his neck. \'93I would not want it said I made a liar of you,\'94 she whispered in a husky voice. \'93Give me an hour, and meet me in my bedchamber.\'94 
\par \'93We waited long enough.\'94 He thrust his fingers inside the bodice of her gown and yanked, and the silk parted with a ripping sound so loud that Cersei was afraid that half of the Red Keep must have heard it. \'93
Take off the rest before I tear that too,\'94 he said. \'93You can keep the crown on. I like you in the crown.\'94
