\par \'93Whatever his offense.\'94 The High Septon repeated the words slowly, weighing them. \'93Strange to say, Your Grace, the more diligently we applied the scourge, the more Ser Osney\rquote 
s offenses seemed to change. He would now have us believe that he never touched Margaery Tyrell. Is that not so, Ser Osney?\'94 
\par Osney Kettleblack opened his eyes. When he saw the queen standing there before him he ran his tongue across his swollen lips, and said, \'93The Wall. You promised me the Wall.\'94 
\par \'93He is mad,\'94 said Cersei. \'93You have driven him mad.\'94 
\par \'93Ser Osney,\'94 said the High Septon, in a firm, clear voice, \'93did you have carnal knowledge of the queen?\'94 
\par \'93Aye.\'94 The chains rattled softly as Osney twisted in his shackles. \'93That one there. She\rquote s the queen I fucked, the one sent me to kill 
the old High Septon. He never had no guards. I just come in when he was sleeping and pushed a pillow down across his face.\'94 
\par Cersei whirled, and ran. 
\par The High Septon tried to seize her, but he was some old sparrow and she was a lioness of the Rock. She pushed him aside and burst through the door, slamming it behind her with a }{\cs28\i clang}{. }{\cs28\i 
The Kettleblacks, I need the Kettleblacks, I will send in Osfryd with the gold cloaks and Osmund with the Kingsguard, Osney will deny it all once they cut him free, and I\rquote ll rid myself of this High Septon just as I did the other.}{
 The four old septas blocked her way and clutched at her with wrinkled hands. She knocked one to the floor and clawed another across the face, and gained the steps. Halfway up, she remembered Taena Merryweather. It made her stumble, panting. }{\cs28\i 
Seven save me,}{ she prayed. }{\cs28\i Taena knows it all. If they take her too, and whip her . . . }{
\par She ran as far as the sept, but no farther. There were women waiting for her there, more septas and silent sisters too, younger than the four old crones below. \'93I am the }{\cs28\i queen,}{\'94 she shouted, backing away from them. \'93
I will have your heads for this, I will have all your heads. Let me pass.\'94 Instead, they laid hands upon her. Cersei ran to the altar of the Mother, but they caught her
